node.text: Artist, musician, and surfer, Alex Knost (@Knostthankyou) has been experimenting in surfing’s subculture for over a decade. Regardless of the medium, he often challenges relationships between texture and color while breaking the regiment of art forms. For this project, he created a film of surfing and the exploration of dissonant sounds.

🎥 @Fox_in_Soks / @JimmyLees

node.text:
Quiet, humble, and recognized by his peers as one of the most well-rounded surfers in the world. @Imaikalani_deVault lets his surfing speak for itself. Watch the first of his two-part section, filmed entirely at home in Hawaii.

🎥 @MauiMarcc / @MylesLaurion

🎵 Inward Oceans | The White Mink Coats

node.text: There’s limited ways to avoid cyclone swell crowds at Noosa. During the filming for Pentacoastal, @WadeGoodall, @HarryBryant, and @KyussKing wired up a car battery and spotlight to pair with a full moon, for some after hours fun. 🎥 @ShaneFletcher
